articles.content: Autopay feels like one of life’s little luxuries. For most recurring expenses, it’s a no-brainer — why not make life easier?. Find Out: 4 Secrets of the Truly Wealthy, According To Dave Ramsey. Here’s the twist, though: Not every bill should be set up for autopay. Some expenses are better managed manually, especially when the amounts fluctuate, errors are common or oversight is essential. “Autopay is convenient, but my millionaire clients are very selective about which bills they put on autopilot.
